title: Live: Banned Dons back v Pies in preseason opener

text:
Daicos lives on for Pies 1:04 Live AFL: JLT Community Series Week 1, Collingwood v Essendon, live scores, updates and videos February 16, 2017 2:31pm by Staff writers Source: FOX SPORTS FOOTY fans will get their first taste of AFL action for 2017 tonight as traditional rivals Collingwood and Essendon clash at Etihad Stadium. 
The opening game of the JLT Community Series has been hotly anticipated for the returns of a multitude of suspended players. 
Lachie Keeffe was named in the Magpies’ squad following a two-year ban for testing positive to banned drug clenbuterol. 
Meanwhile seven of the ten players remaining at Essendon who missed a year for doping bans, including former skipper Jobe Watson and new captain Dyson Heppell, will return. 
ULTIMATE GUIDE: Everything you need to know about the pre-season competition 
The Bombers have named a strong side as they look to work on their chemistry while the Pies will be without first-choice midfielders Scott Pendlebury, Adam Treloar and Taylor Adams. 
It will be our first chance to see the AFL’s new rules for 2017 including stricter interpretations on deliberate rushed behinds and players trying to receive free kicks for being tackled high, as well as the ban on the third man up in ruck contests.
